items.html: The Food & Home card makes it easy to save. Each month, you get a set amount of money to help you pay for food, utility bills, mortgage, or rent.
Check if you get the Food & Home card
See your What to Know About Your Plan booklet to find out:
See your What to Know About Your Plan booklet
• If your plan includes the Food & Home card
• If you get the card automatically or only with a qualifying health condition
You can use your Food & Home card to pay for:
• Utility bills, like your home's gas or electric bill

Choose to spend your money all at once or throughout the month. Either way, be sure to use the full amount — you can’t roll over unused money to the next month. We automatically refill your card on the first of each month, so make sure you don’t throw it away!
so make sure you don’t throw it away!
If your plan automatically includes the card, you’ll get it in the mail.
If your plan requires that you qualify for the card, do one of the following:
Complete the qualification form online
• Call us at 1-800-338-6833 (TTY 711)
Once you get your card, follow the instructions it comes with to activate it.
online at Healthy Benefits
• Choose foods like fruits, veggies, fish, meat, eggs, and more
• Ask the cashier to scan the barcode on the back of your Food & Home card or in the Healthy Benefits+ app
You can only use your card at participating stores — not at convenience stores, restaurants (including fast food), or gas stations.
How to pay utility bills, mortgage, or rent
• If your service provider accepts Visa, you can use your 16-digit card number like a credit or debit card and pay them directly. Payment will go through right away.
• If your service provider is set up with Healthy Benefits, you can pay online with Healthy Benefits. Payment may take up to 7 days, so pay at least a week before the due date.
pay online with Healthy Benefits
• If the bill is more than your benefit amount, send the rest of your payment directly to your service provider
• If there’s a processing fee when you pay, we'll use part of your monthly benefit to cover it
• If your service provider doesn’t accept Visa and isn't set up with Healthy Benefits, you may not be able to use your benefit to pay them
• You can use your card for mortgage or rent only if your bank or landlord can accept Food & Home card payment
How much money do I get each month?
Check your What to Know About Your Plan booklet
Can I use the benefit before my card arrives?
online with Healthy Benefits
Nope, just give the card to the cashier and ask them to scan the barcode on the back. If you’re ever asked to enter a PIN, it’s the last 4 digits of the card number.
Do I need to spend the full amount all at once?
Nope. You can spend it however you want throughout the month, but be sure to spend it all — you can’t roll over unused money to the next month.
Check your balance online or call the number on the back of your card
Check your balance online
Will I get a new card each month?
No, so be sure to hold onto your card. We automatically add more money to it on the first of each month.
Do I have to use the card to pay?
online with Healthy Benefits
Are there any limits on what foods I can buy?
You can buy any foods you choose, but we recommend sticking with items like:
• Eggs, cheese, milk, and other dairy products
• Whole grains, like whole wheat bread and brown rice
You can’t use your card for certain items, including alcohol, baby formula, pet food, or household goods like paper towels.

You can pay most common bills like natural gas, electric, water, sewer, garbage, internet, cable, and cell phone. You can not use your card on prepaid phone service, firewood, pellet fuel, or gasoline for your car.
Can I pay bills for other people?
No, you can only pay bills for yourself.
visit Healthy Benefits online
For questions about whether you qualify for the card, text us at 866-85 or call us at 1-800-338-6833 (TTY 711).
Devoted Health Guides are here 8am to 8pm, 7 days a week.
Or call us at 1-800-DEVOTED (338–6833) TTY 711
